Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Add gather support for cross host recv, so that multiple senders can write into a single buffer, thus avoiding a subsequent stack, and limiting the number of independent PjRtBuffers needed for a data exchange.

The gathered buffers must form a contiguous range in the destination buffer, but they may be smaller than the full buffer in which case the trailing portion of the buffer contains undefined data. If the trailing portion needs to be padded with a specific value (e.g., zero) the padding should be done using a subsequent TPU program.

For now the slice boundaries must be known at the time that the receive is enqueued. If necessary we may add another API later that would allow individual slice receives to be enqueued, so that some receives could begin before all slice sizes are known.

[{"sha":"e5ae83e503e81baec32f71ae5e775d414ba76ded","author":{"name":"Sebastiaan van Stijn","email":"64b2b6d12bfe4baae7dad3d018f8cbf6b0e7a044@gone.nl"},"message":"volumes: only send "create" event when actually creating volume

The VolumesService did not have information wether or not a volume
was _created_ or if a volume already existed in the driver, and
the existing volume was used.

As a result, multiple "create" events could be generated for the
same volume. For example:

1. Run `docker events` in a shell to start listening for events
2. Create a volume:

    docker volume create myvolume

3. Start a container that uses that volume:

    docker run -dit -v myvolume:/foo busybox

4. Check the events that were generated:

    2021-02-15T18:49:55.874621004+01:00 volume create myvolume (driver=local)
    2021-02-15T18:50:11.442759052+01:00 volume create myvolume (driver=local)
    2021-02-15T18:50:11.487104176+01:00 container create 45112157c8b1382626bf5e01ef18445a4c680f3846c5e32d01775dddee8ca6d1 (image=busybox, name=gracious_hypatia)
    2021-02-15T18:50:11.519288102+01:00 network connect a19f6bb8d44ff84d478670fa4e34c5bf5305f42786294d3d90e790ac74b6d3e0 (container=45112157c8b1382626bf5e01ef18445a4c680f3846c5e32d01775dddee8ca6d1, name=bridge, type=bridge)
    2021-02-15T18:50:11.526407799+01:00 volume mount myvolume (container=45112157c8b1382626bf5e01ef18445a4c680f3846c5e32d01775dddee8ca6d1, destination=/foo, driver=local, propagation=, read/write=true)
    2021-02-15T18:50:11.864134043+01:00 container start 45112157c8b1382626bf5e01ef18445a4c680f3846c5e32d01775dddee8ca6d1 (image=busybox, name=gracious_hypatia)

5. Notice that a "volume create" event is created twice;

    - once when `docker volume create` was ran
    - once when `docker run ...` was ran

This patch moves the generation of (most) events to the volume _store_, and only
generates an event if the volume did not yet exist.

Signed-off-by: Sebastiaan van Stijn <github@gone.nl>","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/moby/moby/commits/e5ae83e503e81baec32f71ae5e775d414ba76ded"},{"sha":"ef4d473401421d26633d43547b4a28978887386a","author":{"name":"Sebastiaan van Stijn","email":"2b34a3e3e055981c6c83bcd4f9afd06751b4ac0e@users.noreply.github.com"},"message":"Merge pull request #42028 from thaJeztah/fix_duplicate_volume_event

[{"sha":"aecb3b6d114e8fafddf6982133737198e8ea7cb3","author":{"name":"Andrew Clark","email":"46f1a0bd5592a2f9244ca321b129902a06b53e03@andrewclark.io"},"message":"Deprecate ReactDOM.render and ReactDOM.hydrate (#21652)

* Use existing test warning filter for server tests

We have a warning filter for our internal tests to ignore warnings
that are too noisy or that we haven't removed from our test suite yet:
shouldIgnoreConsoleError.

Many of our server rendering tests don't use this filter, though,
because it has its own special of asserting warnings.

So I added the warning filter to the server tests, too.

* Deprecate ReactDOM.render and ReactDOM.hydrate

These are no longer supported in React 18. They are replaced by the
`createRoot` API.

The warning includes a link to documentation of the new API. Currently
it redirects to the corresponding working group post. Here's the PR to
set up the redirect: https://github.com/reactjs/reactjs.org/pull/3730

Many of our tests still use ReactDOM.render. We will need to gradually
migrate them over to createRoot.

In the meantime, I added the warnings to our internal warning filter.","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/facebook/react/commits/aecb3b6d114e8fafddf6982133737198e8ea7cb3"}]

We are support three main apply points for KPLs
 - inside a single model with both preprocessing and trainable layers
 - in a Dataset.map when calling model.fit on a Dataset
 - in a Dataset.map when calling model.fit on a DatasetCreator

strategies they support.
